headline: Delta sues cybersecurity firm CrowdStrike over tech outage that canceled flights
summary: Delta Air Lines sued CrowdStrike on Friday, claiming the cybersecurity company had cut corners and caused a worldwide technology outage that led to thousands of canceled flight in July.  The airline is asking for compensation and punitive damages from the outage, which started with a faulty update sent to several million Microsoft computers.  Delta said the outage crippled its operations for several days, costing more than $500 million in lost revenue and extra expenses.
